last_episode_to_air.name: The Impossibility of Forever?
last_episode_to_air.overview: Love, career, and a home of her own: Isobel's New York City dreams are finally coming true. But is it possible to have them all at once, or even in one place?

name: Strangers
overview: Meet Isobel. Struggling to make rent, she turns her extra bedroom into extra cash - all while trying to figure out exactly who she is. Spoiler alert: It's complicated. Strangers is a coming-out-of-age story about finding yourself.

episodes.name: Honeymooners
episodes.overview: A newly-single Isobel rents out her spare bedroom to a honeymooning couple who isn’t exactly looking for some alone time.

episodes.name: Tinder Hearts
episodes.overview: Isobel and her BFF Cam swap their expertise about what’s wrong with Hollywood for some treats that lead to dancing. Isobel unexpectedly meets someone while tripping at said dance class.

episodes.name: Water Into Wine
episodes.overview: Isobel’s date doesn't go as planned thanks to the overbearing minister of a new-age post-gender-binary religion, an overly-friendly Cam and an unannounced visit.

episodes.name: Couples Counselling
episodes.overview: Isobel and Cam work through their biggest fight to date with the help of Isobel’s latest renter, Kim, a couple’s counselor. They are encouraged to have a day of friendship to heal, and return home to find an unexpected visitor in Isobel’s living room.

episodes.name: Hot Set
episodes.overview: Isobel and Jake wake to find themselves in the midst of an Indie film. Seeing Hailey again gives Isobel the courage to speak up for what she wants.

episodes.name: Get Away
episodes.overview: When Haley and Isobel take a trip together, Isobel enjoys renting for a change and confronts expressing her feelings for Haley in public.

episodes.name: Homeless
episodes.overview: After being evicted from her home, Isobel must figure out her future, while helping her final renter, Emmy, a wandering musician, locate her birth mother. Isobel learns to say goodbye.

episodes.name: The Big (Gr)apple
episodes.overview: Isobel and Cam have made the big move to New York City together, but quickly find their experiences couldn't be more different. When their apartment search gets tricky, Isobel has to get creative.

episodes.name: Open Mari(age)
episodes.overview: Isobel finds herself homeless in NYC when reality comes crashing through the floorboards. With the help of her new work friend, Iso goes to stay with a boxer in Bed Stuy. She rolls with the punches when she meets a gorgeous woman who might not be as available as she would have hoped.

episodes.name: Maskulinity
episodes.overview: Isobel lands her first writing job, navigates her new relationship with Mari, and oversteps when she stays with a family trying to reconcile with their son's homosexuality in Richmond Hill, Queens.

episodes.name: The Disappearance of Katia Romaine
episodes.overview: Homeless yet again, Isobel lands in Brighton Beach, Brooklyn with a new host (Vlad) who creates Escape Rooms for a living. But when a double date goes horribly wrong, there’s no escaping the reality that Isobel and Cam’s friendship might be over and that Isobel needs more from Mari.

episodes.name: Big Little Chill
episodes.overview: Isobel is thrilled to be invited to a special weekend upstate with Mari's friends. But she quickly learns that leaving the city doesn't mean avoiding Mari's past and present, and starts to wonder if their relationship even has a future.

episodes.name: Smash the Plate-triarchy
episodes.overview: Valentine's Day and Lunar New Year converge when Isobel stays with a newly single mom in Tribeca. With Mari away, things heat up between Isobel and Milo, and Isobel gets a surprise visit from her family, as well as some motherly advice she wasn't asking for.

episodes.name: West Side Highway
episodes.overview: Spring comes early and so does Mari, surprising Isobel just when she was ready to move on. There's music in the air on the Upper West Side, where Isobel's latest BnB host, a composer, inspires Isobel to consider the possibility of new beginnings.

episodes.name: First Skate
episodes.overview: With her hosts away for the weekend, Isobel has a fabulous Red Hook loft all to herself - but not for long. When their college-student daughter stops by, she pulls Isobel into a day of distraction and a night of partying. Their bender leads to complications in her relationships with Mari and Milo.

episodes.name: Spun and Done
episodes.overview: Isobel turns 30 and celebrates with a wild last night of her 20s, but when carefree becomes careless, she endangers her relationship with Milo and her own sense of self. An all-nighter leads her on an unexpected trek through the city, at the end of which she finds even more than she was looking for.

episodes.name: The Impossibility of Forever?
episodes.overview: Love, career, and a home of her own: Isobel's New York City dreams are finally coming true. But is it possible to have them all at once, or even in one place?
